1
00:01:31,410 --> 00:01:34,048
=The Glamorous Night=

2
00:01:35,880 --> 00:01:36,824
How were you driving?

3
00:01:36,824 --> 00:01:37,904
How were you riding?

4
00:01:38,065 --> 00:01:39,505
You shouldn't be passing from here.

5
00:01:39,744 --> 00:01:40,585
You knocked me over.

6
00:01:40,665 --> 00:01:41,505
You passed from here.

7
00:01:41,505 --> 00:01:42,344
What are you doing?

8
00:01:42,344 --> 00:01:43,264
You squeezed through.

9
00:01:46,225 --> 00:01:47,744
I have to deliver this order.

10
00:01:47,744 --> 00:01:48,744
Pay for my car now.

11
00:01:48,865 --> 00:01:50,425
Hurry up, pay for my car.

12
00:01:50,585 --> 00:01:51,945
Hurry up. I'm in a hurry.

13
00:01:51,945 --> 00:01:52,945
The customer

14
00:01:53,184 --> 00:01:53,904
will complain.

15
00:01:53,904 --> 00:01:55,225
I have a passenger.

16
00:01:55,225 --> 00:01:56,544
What if the customer complains?

17
00:01:57,225 --> 00:01:58,705
It's not your problem.

18
00:01:59,025 --> 00:01:59,945
Hurry. Pay up.

19
00:01:59,945 --> 00:02:01,624
You should pay me.

20
00:02:01,624 --> 00:02:02,544
You wrecked my car.

21
00:02:02,544 --> 00:02:03,505
I'm injured.

22
00:02:03,505 --> 00:02:04,984
You crashed into my car.

23
00:02:04,984 --> 00:02:05,904
What else do you want?

24
00:02:09,064 --> 00:02:10,504
(Anxiety and insomnia)

25
00:02:12,025 --> 00:02:13,705
(coupled with endless rain.)

26
00:02:15,025 --> 00:02:16,624
(This is what Paz wrote in his poem.)

27
00:02:17,744 --> 00:02:19,425
(Not Andalusia's swans,)

28
00:02:20,985 --> 00:02:22,184
(nor the splendid birds.)

29
00:02:23,585 --> 00:02:24,664
(Birds have wings.)

30
00:02:26,064 --> 00:02:27,224
(Humans have sorrow.)

31
00:02:29,224 --> 00:02:31,825
(Grinding away
has reached new levels of exhaustion.)

32
00:02:33,224 --> 00:02:35,504
(I fell asleep
on the yoga mat at the gym,)

33
00:02:36,305 --> 00:02:38,385
(then woke up freezing.)

34
00:02:39,624 --> 00:02:40,664
(This place is so cold.)

35
00:02:41,865 --> 00:02:43,184
(It's only late November)

36
00:02:44,265 --> 00:02:45,928
(and it's already 13 degrees Celsius.)

37
00:03:00,034 --> 00:03:03,272
=Episode 15=
(Hunting Game)

38
00:03:05,504 --> 00:03:07,344
Waiter, two more bottles of wine.

39
00:03:08,545 --> 00:03:09,025
Mao.

40
00:03:11,064 --> 00:03:11,825
Tang, what's up?

41
00:03:14,464 --> 00:03:16,145
The big boss just visited our store

42
00:03:16,904 --> 00:03:18,664
and saw someone buy 96 bottles of wine.

43
00:03:18,865 --> 00:03:22,224
What a coincidence.
Was it one of our own?

44
00:03:23,064 --> 00:03:24,145
No, it wasn't.

45
00:03:26,025 --> 00:03:27,624
T-This means we made a sale.

46
00:03:27,985 --> 00:03:30,064
Who can afford 96 bottles in one go?

47
00:03:30,265 --> 00:03:31,865
Someone who buys 96 bottles

48
00:03:31,865 --> 00:03:33,305
isn't buying liquor.

49
00:03:33,305 --> 00:03:34,865
That's stocking up.

50
00:03:35,064 --> 00:03:36,425
Tang Lide is done for this time.

51
00:03:36,944 --> 00:03:38,545
Barry will audit his accounts.

52
00:03:39,464 --> 00:03:41,585
Serves him right
for coming after me first.

53
00:03:42,744 --> 00:03:45,504
He even tried to get my clients
to buy from Dong Yue.

54
00:03:45,985 --> 00:03:46,825
In his dreams.

55
00:03:50,865 --> 00:03:53,464
Didn't you ever
think about winning him over?

56
00:03:54,265 --> 00:03:55,425
The way he operates...

57
00:03:55,425 --> 00:03:58,224
Even if he helped me
become Sales Director,

58
00:03:58,224 --> 00:04:00,025
I wouldn't dare keep him on the team.

59
00:04:12,145 --> 00:04:12,865
You know what?

60
00:04:13,865 --> 00:04:17,304
That fierce look in your eyes
is really tempting.

61
00:04:18,984 --> 00:04:19,625
My back hurts.

62
00:04:23,705 --> 00:04:24,544
Go on.

63
00:04:24,705 --> 00:04:25,544
I'm going to rest.

64
00:04:41,145 --> 00:04:45,705
Your back hurts.
Why do I also feel something?

65
00:04:46,705 --> 00:04:47,304
Peter.

66
00:04:48,065 --> 00:04:48,984
You know me.

67
00:04:48,984 --> 00:04:51,664
Can you give me another chance?

68
00:04:51,664 --> 00:04:53,864
I know you like playing tricks.

69
00:04:54,104 --> 00:04:56,424
But I didn't expect you to go this far.

70
00:04:56,825 --> 00:04:59,424
Company-owned stores
were Barry's pioneering venture.

71
00:04:59,825 --> 00:05:01,464
He always thought the sales were great

72
00:05:01,745 --> 00:05:03,304
and reported them to headquarters.

73
00:05:03,945 --> 00:05:04,745
And now?

74
00:05:05,864 --> 00:05:08,224
You took over eight months ago.

75
00:05:08,544 --> 00:05:12,705
All those sales were made
from the budget allocated to you.

76
00:05:13,544 --> 00:05:14,705
What were you thinking?

77
00:05:16,745 --> 00:05:18,145
Barry even criticized me.

78
00:05:19,224 --> 00:05:20,984
Asia-Pacific is watching us now.

79
00:05:21,544 --> 00:05:22,984
The internal audit team is coming.

80
00:05:25,224 --> 00:05:25,745
I'm sorry.

81
00:05:26,304 --> 00:05:27,145
Resign.

82
00:05:56,784 --> 00:05:58,585
I'm so happy

83
00:05:59,265 --> 00:06:00,104
and excited.

84
00:06:02,104 --> 00:06:04,385
I managed to take over
Tang Lide's position

85
00:06:04,664 --> 00:06:06,945
all thanks to your support and help.

86
00:06:07,344 --> 00:06:08,664
No, we should thank you.

87
00:06:09,265 --> 00:06:10,984
Yeah, we need to thank you.

88
00:06:11,344 --> 00:06:12,585
You gave us the heads-up.

89
00:06:12,585 --> 00:06:15,265
Otherwise, we wouldn't know
he was faking the sales figures.

90
00:06:16,344 --> 00:06:16,904
Well,

91
00:06:17,145 --> 00:06:19,585
I was scared about what he was doing.

92
00:06:19,585 --> 00:06:21,864
This would come out eventually, right?

93
00:06:22,984 --> 00:06:23,945
Come on, that's it.

94
00:06:24,224 --> 00:06:24,984
A toast to you.

95
00:06:25,344 --> 00:06:27,224
I'll be counting

96
00:06:27,784 --> 00:06:28,585
on your support.

97
00:06:30,864 --> 00:06:31,424
Same here.

98
00:06:32,104 --> 00:06:32,864
Same here.

99
00:06:37,945 --> 00:06:38,784
For table one.

100
00:06:39,145 --> 00:06:39,505
Okay.

101
00:06:47,464 --> 00:06:49,185
When did you add each other on WeChat?

102
00:06:50,664 --> 00:06:51,904
On the day of the interview.

103
00:06:54,224 --> 00:06:55,984
It seems she's not in Guangzhou.

104
00:06:55,984 --> 00:06:56,825
Business trip?

105
00:06:58,224 --> 00:06:59,864
She seems to be in the north.

106
00:07:01,424 --> 00:07:02,825
I hope she never comes back.

107
00:07:04,664 --> 00:07:06,104
Judging from her August posts,

108
00:07:06,104 --> 00:07:07,984
Li Dongming didn't know her back then.

109
00:07:08,065 --> 00:07:09,825
Isn't that how office romances go?

110
00:07:10,625 --> 00:07:11,984
They act all proper in public.

111
00:07:11,984 --> 00:07:14,185
But who knows how far things go
behind closed doors?

112
00:07:15,224 --> 00:07:18,344
Pretending not to know each other
is part of the game.

113
00:07:22,385 --> 00:07:23,864
Give up if you can't take it anymore.

114
00:07:24,224 --> 00:07:25,544
I'm worried you'll be twisted.

115
00:07:25,544 --> 00:07:27,025
I've been twisted for ages.

116
00:07:28,104 --> 00:07:29,505
I didn't even need a push.

117
00:07:29,745 --> 00:07:31,224
Look at people in our line of work.

118
00:07:31,705 --> 00:07:32,904
We wear the thickest makeup

119
00:07:32,904 --> 00:07:34,864
and sleep later than the world.

120
00:07:34,945 --> 00:07:36,864
We drink Class 1 carcinogens every day.

121
00:07:36,945 --> 00:07:38,185
Why wouldn't I be twisted?

122
00:07:39,385 --> 00:07:40,984
Cheers to you, you twisted woman.

123
00:07:45,505 --> 00:07:47,544
But Qiao Hailun is quite busy, too.

124
00:07:47,745 --> 00:07:48,825
Look at her posts.

125
00:07:49,304 --> 00:07:51,104
She's either working late or traveling.

126
00:07:51,505 --> 00:07:54,544
She almost got hit by a car
while rushing to catch a flight.

127
00:07:55,265 --> 00:07:56,385
It made me feel so...

128
00:07:58,424 --> 00:08:00,104
Why is she having so much work?

129
00:08:00,265 --> 00:08:01,304
That's why I don't know

130
00:08:01,304 --> 00:08:02,945
why she's with Li Dongming.

131
00:08:03,505 --> 00:08:04,625
For someone like him,

132
00:08:04,625 --> 00:08:06,025
power comes first, money second.

133
00:08:06,304 --> 00:08:08,304
No matter how close she gets to him,

134
00:08:08,505 --> 00:08:10,664
he won't even let her
skip a single slide.

135
00:08:10,825 --> 00:08:12,585
That's how all consulting bosses are.

136
00:08:14,065 --> 00:08:15,664
Li Dongming might even be a nice one.

137
00:08:15,864 --> 00:08:18,265
With another boss,
she might not even make any money.

138
00:08:19,904 --> 00:08:21,745
Even unspoken rules
are getting competitive.

139
00:08:24,265 --> 00:08:25,025
Serves her right.

140
00:08:25,984 --> 00:08:28,984
But why did she suddenly
ask you for an interview

141
00:08:28,984 --> 00:08:30,065
and add you

142
00:08:30,065 --> 00:08:30,585
on WeChat?

143
00:08:31,864 --> 00:08:33,584
Does she want you
to confront Li Dongming

144
00:08:33,584 --> 00:08:34,745
so she can take your place?

145
00:08:38,184 --> 00:08:38,904
No idea.

146
00:08:39,544 --> 00:08:40,105
It's strange.

147
00:08:40,704 --> 00:08:42,505
She probably just wants attention.

148
00:08:43,145 --> 00:08:44,385
She's dating Li Dongming,

149
00:08:45,145 --> 00:08:47,385
managing projects
of the company his wife works for,

150
00:08:47,424 --> 00:08:49,304
interviewing her in person,

151
00:08:49,304 --> 00:08:51,704
and evaluating her performance.

152
00:08:52,064 --> 00:08:53,865
She might even work with Li Dongming

153
00:08:53,865 --> 00:08:56,105
to help get his wife promoted.

154
00:08:56,105 --> 00:08:57,385
Yet through all this,

155
00:08:57,385 --> 00:08:59,184
his wife doesn't even know she exists.

156
00:08:59,544 --> 00:09:00,544
How frustrating.

157
00:09:01,304 --> 00:09:02,664
She has to show herself.

158
00:09:09,184 --> 00:09:10,704
You just went full rap mode.

159
00:09:11,824 --> 00:09:13,584
You kept saying "his wife"

160
00:09:13,584 --> 00:09:15,184
as if it weren't you.

161
00:09:19,505 --> 00:09:20,505
In my heart,

162
00:09:22,865 --> 00:09:24,784
I'm no longer Li Dongming's wife.

163
00:09:27,505 --> 00:09:29,064
Then who are you?

164
00:09:29,064 --> 00:09:29,640
A shareholder.

165
00:09:32,105 --> 00:09:34,184
We co-founded a company

166
00:09:34,505 --> 00:09:35,865
as shareholders.

167
00:09:36,424 --> 00:09:38,664
I'm very displeased with him now.

168
00:09:39,985 --> 00:09:41,225
But still, he has his uses.

169
00:09:41,225 --> 00:09:42,664
He brings in money.

170
00:09:44,704 --> 00:09:45,625
So I'll put up with it.

171
00:09:48,064 --> 00:09:49,345
When I can't take it anymore,

172
00:09:49,345 --> 00:09:50,784
I'll just wave goodbye.

173
00:09:52,784 --> 00:09:53,544
Brilliant.

174
00:09:53,865 --> 00:09:54,424
Great mindset.

175
00:09:55,145 --> 00:09:56,105
So by your logic,

176
00:09:56,105 --> 00:09:59,385
you guys are running
a limited liability partnership.

177
00:09:59,465 --> 00:10:03,385
And I'm running a sole proprietorship?

178
00:10:07,265 --> 00:10:08,105
You?

179
00:10:08,584 --> 00:10:12,784
You're the unicorn startup
about to get acquired.

180
00:10:23,176 --> 00:10:23,931
Hello?

181
00:10:25,985 --> 00:10:28,944
What? Joint internal audit team?

182
00:10:44,505 --> 00:10:45,025
Come in.

183
00:10:52,304 --> 00:10:52,784
Ms. Qi.

184
00:10:54,064 --> 00:10:55,424
Sorry, one second.

185
00:10:56,145 --> 00:10:56,745
Ms. Qi.

186
00:10:57,145 --> 00:10:58,784
Headquarters
and Asia-Pacific sent people.

187
00:11:03,664 --> 00:11:04,424
I don't understand.

188
00:11:05,105 --> 00:11:07,105
You've been working here
for over a month.

189
00:11:08,025 --> 00:11:09,505
If you've found nothing,

190
00:11:10,265 --> 00:11:11,505
you should be wrapping up,

191
00:11:11,745 --> 00:11:13,704
instead of bringing in more people

192
00:11:14,385 --> 00:11:15,505
and extending your stay.

193
00:11:17,385 --> 00:11:19,505
It's not like we didn't find anything.

194
00:11:19,505 --> 00:11:20,304
On the contrary,

195
00:11:20,465 --> 00:11:22,544
we've uncovered very serious issues

196
00:11:22,664 --> 00:11:24,904
not just in the China division.

197
00:11:25,465 --> 00:11:27,824
(Yang Huiling)
This is why Huiling joined us.

198
00:11:28,385 --> 00:11:30,920
(GST Liquor Asia-Pacific Investigator)
She's experienced in

199
00:11:30,920 --> 00:11:32,025
anti-fraud investigations.

200
00:11:32,025 --> 00:11:32,625
Wait.

201
00:11:34,664 --> 00:11:35,976
Not just in the China division?

202
00:11:36,584 --> 00:11:37,304
What do you mean?

203
00:11:37,465 --> 00:11:39,944
I can't discuss that with you.

204
00:11:41,505 --> 00:11:44,265
We will arrange private communication
with some employees.

205
00:11:44,865 --> 00:11:45,424
Of course.

206
00:11:45,664 --> 00:11:48,424
The content of communication
will be strictly confidential.

207
00:11:48,824 --> 00:11:49,784
Even from me?

208
00:11:50,025 --> 00:11:50,784
Yes.

209
00:11:50,784 --> 00:11:51,505
This won't do.

210
00:11:51,944 --> 00:11:53,320
I will tell the headquarters.

211
00:11:53,465 --> 00:11:54,904
I want you to leave immediately.

212
00:11:55,505 --> 00:11:56,105
Sorry.

213
00:11:56,105 --> 00:11:57,664
I have something to report to Barry.

214
00:11:57,664 --> 00:11:59,145
Please step out for a moment.

215
00:11:59,145 --> 00:11:59,784
Okay.

216
00:12:00,025 --> 00:12:00,824
Sun Yu, please stay.

217
00:12:01,145 --> 00:12:02,625
Alright, we'll talk later.

218
00:12:13,025 --> 00:12:13,625
Explain it.

219
00:12:14,664 --> 00:12:15,784
Explain to the boss.

220
00:12:17,265 --> 00:12:20,265
We looked into Xu Yuntian's accounts

221
00:12:20,865 --> 00:12:23,145
and identified
several suspicious transactions

222
00:12:23,745 --> 00:12:25,064
of large amounts.

223
00:12:25,865 --> 00:12:28,985
We could hand it over
to the Economic Investigation.

224
00:12:29,505 --> 00:12:32,865
But the company disapproved of it.

225
00:12:32,865 --> 00:12:35,345
Of course, we shouldn't
air our dirty laundry in public.

226
00:12:35,625 --> 00:12:36,184
That's right.

227
00:12:36,865 --> 00:12:38,064
So we didn't report it.

228
00:12:38,465 --> 00:12:40,265
But Gao Jiawei is from the Asia-Pacific.

229
00:12:40,265 --> 00:12:41,625
And he operates independently.

230
00:12:42,265 --> 00:12:44,064
He reported it to the Asia-Pacific.

231
00:12:44,784 --> 00:12:47,345
So there's nothing we can do.

232
00:12:47,625 --> 00:12:49,064
We can't kick them out.

233
00:12:49,745 --> 00:12:50,625
Otherwise,

234
00:12:50,985 --> 00:12:54,265
headquarters would think
we're hiding something.

235
00:12:54,625 --> 00:12:55,345
Alright.

236
00:12:56,345 --> 00:12:57,145
Got it.

237
00:12:58,265 --> 00:12:59,625
Now I have no choice.

238
00:13:00,865 --> 00:13:02,625
Sun Yu, excuse me.

239
00:13:03,105 --> 00:13:03,985
Please step out.

240
00:13:03,985 --> 00:13:04,625
Okay.

241
00:13:10,145 --> 00:13:11,745
I don't trust him.

242
00:13:12,145 --> 00:13:13,145
I know.

243
00:13:13,145 --> 00:13:15,704
But we can't target
so many executives at once.

244
00:13:16,265 --> 00:13:17,544
Give me a bit more time.

245
00:13:17,544 --> 00:13:18,865
Let me take it slowly, okay?

246
00:13:25,145 --> 00:13:25,904
Mr. Mao.

247
00:13:26,265 --> 00:13:27,505
Give me a break.

248
00:13:27,505 --> 00:13:28,784
Stop teasing me.

249
00:13:29,145 --> 00:13:30,265
How am I teasing you?

250
00:13:30,265 --> 00:13:31,544
I'm completely sincere.

251
00:13:32,025 --> 00:13:34,745
I've been waiting forever
for that idiot to get fired.

252
00:13:37,784 --> 00:13:39,505
The internal audit team just notified us

253
00:13:39,505 --> 00:13:41,784
to compile all the sales data.

254
00:13:42,025 --> 00:13:43,745
They're deadly serious.

255
00:13:44,385 --> 00:13:45,625
Have you seen the news?

256
00:13:45,985 --> 00:13:49,025
Several bosses of foreign-invested
companies were taken away.

257
00:13:49,784 --> 00:13:51,345
Yeah, so terrifying.

258
00:13:51,345 --> 00:13:52,625
Imagine working one day

259
00:13:52,625 --> 00:13:53,704
and being put in prison.

260
00:13:54,704 --> 00:13:55,265
Scared?

261
00:13:56,265 --> 00:13:57,025
Nonsense.

262
00:13:57,385 --> 00:13:58,745
I'm just a small fry.

263
00:13:58,784 --> 00:13:59,944
Let the boss panic.

264
00:14:03,904 --> 00:14:04,505
Mr. Sun.

265
00:14:04,625 --> 00:14:05,505
- What brings you here?
- May I come in?

266
00:14:05,625 --> 00:14:06,225
Have a seat.

267
00:14:06,225 --> 00:14:06,865
Okay.

268
00:14:07,025 --> 00:14:07,784
Want a drink?

269
00:14:07,865 --> 00:14:08,505
No, thanks.

270
00:14:08,865 --> 00:14:10,265
I'll just say a few words.

271
00:14:11,025 --> 00:14:11,865
Here's the thing.

272
00:14:12,385 --> 00:14:14,985
Recently, someone reported
to the internal audit team

273
00:14:15,225 --> 00:14:19,584
that you're dating
a first-tier distributor's daughter.

274
00:14:20,625 --> 00:14:21,105
Yeah.

275
00:14:21,105 --> 00:14:23,784
But that's my private life, isn't it?

276
00:14:26,265 --> 00:14:28,025
If you weren't
the Deputy Sales Director,

277
00:14:28,465 --> 00:14:30,105
this would absolutely be your privacy.

278
00:14:30,625 --> 00:14:31,745
But you are.

279
00:14:32,505 --> 00:14:33,385
You should know

280
00:14:34,265 --> 00:14:36,745
that dating a distributor's daughter

281
00:14:37,664 --> 00:14:39,704
creates a conflict of interest.

282
00:14:41,105 --> 00:14:42,225
Our policy requires you

283
00:14:42,664 --> 00:14:43,985
to disclose this earlier.

284
00:14:45,865 --> 00:14:46,865
Don't get me wrong.

285
00:14:47,465 --> 00:14:48,865
I'm not here to interrogate you.

286
00:14:49,465 --> 00:14:50,625
I'm here to remind you.

287
00:14:51,544 --> 00:14:55,184
The internal audit team
will likely investigate this matter.

288
00:14:58,304 --> 00:14:59,145
Then what?

289
00:14:59,745 --> 00:15:00,544
Then...

290
00:15:01,704 --> 00:15:02,625
I don't know either.

291
00:15:06,544 --> 00:15:06,944
That's it.

292
00:15:08,625 --> 00:15:09,225
Take care.

293
00:15:14,385 --> 00:15:16,584
They're investigating
your tie with Shen Xing.

294
00:15:19,225 --> 00:15:20,225
Are you worried?

295
00:15:21,505 --> 00:15:23,625
I'm worried they have ulterior motives.

296
00:15:23,784 --> 00:15:25,904
Although I was dating Shen Xing,

297
00:15:26,025 --> 00:15:30,025
the one doing business with Mr. Shen
was never me.

298
00:15:30,745 --> 00:15:32,145
I know. It was Xu Yuntian.

299
00:15:32,625 --> 00:15:35,664
Barry was eager to eliminate Xu Yuntian

300
00:15:35,865 --> 00:15:38,625
because Xu's ties with Shen Mo
went too deep.

301
00:15:38,625 --> 00:15:41,784
It reached a point
where he could blackmail the company.

302
00:15:43,784 --> 00:15:47,904
I suspect Barry opposed your promotion

303
00:15:48,544 --> 00:15:49,584
and supported Zhao Mei

304
00:15:50,105 --> 00:15:53,985
mainly because
you were too close to Shen Mo.

305
00:15:54,784 --> 00:15:56,625
He can't let you
become another Xu Yuntian.

306
00:15:56,745 --> 00:15:58,505
But I can't cut ties with Mr. Shen.

307
00:15:58,904 --> 00:16:01,465
He generates over 30%
of the company's sales.

308
00:16:01,465 --> 00:16:02,824
The company wants him.

309
00:16:03,025 --> 00:16:04,505
So that's the dilemma.

310
00:16:05,625 --> 00:16:07,145
Just like finding a girlfriend,

311
00:16:07,784 --> 00:16:10,505
every man wants a beautiful lady

312
00:16:11,025 --> 00:16:14,345
but fears her beauty might
attract unwanted attention.

313
00:16:15,025 --> 00:16:18,784
What if I could bring
a group of cooperative distributors

314
00:16:20,025 --> 00:16:20,584
to join us?

315
00:16:22,505 --> 00:16:24,584
We're 30,000 cases short
of our annual target.

316
00:16:25,625 --> 00:16:26,704
I can fix that.

317
00:16:27,145 --> 00:16:28,904
You can handle that?

318
00:16:29,985 --> 00:16:30,745
Without Shen Mo?

319
00:16:31,745 --> 00:16:34,025
Some distributors from Zhongshan
have approached me.

320
00:16:34,784 --> 00:16:37,865
I plan to recommend them to you first.

321
00:16:38,385 --> 00:16:39,465
You can take them to Barry.

322
00:16:40,145 --> 00:16:40,784
How about that?

323
00:16:42,824 --> 00:16:45,345
If Mr. Shen finds out, we're finished.

324
00:16:45,904 --> 00:16:47,544
But he refuses to stock up.

325
00:16:48,745 --> 00:16:49,664
Thirty thousand cases.

326
00:16:50,105 --> 00:16:51,664
We're also finished if we fail.

327
00:16:52,225 --> 00:16:53,064
Yeah.

328
00:16:54,625 --> 00:16:55,904
With or without Shen Mo,

329
00:16:55,985 --> 00:16:57,225
I'm on your side.

330
00:16:57,225 --> 00:17:00,745
I've always wanted you
to take over as Sales Director,

331
00:17:00,784 --> 00:17:01,865
not Zhao Mei.

332
00:17:02,145 --> 00:17:02,904
Thanks, Peter.

333
00:17:12,384 --> 00:17:15,025
So it's serious this time?

334
00:17:16,665 --> 00:17:18,505
We've always been serious.

335
00:17:19,104 --> 00:17:20,745
We used to be more discreet.

336
00:17:21,144 --> 00:17:23,144
This time, it's a bit of a commotion.

337
00:17:23,544 --> 00:17:25,025
Am I right to perceive it

338
00:17:25,025 --> 00:17:29,465
as a trick to smoke out the tiger
and scare the snake?

339
00:17:29,465 --> 00:17:31,144
You've watched too many cop dramas.

340
00:17:32,384 --> 00:17:34,384
A company's books are easy to audit.

341
00:17:34,624 --> 00:17:37,144
To professionals, they're like a sieve.

342
00:17:37,225 --> 00:17:38,344
Full of holes.

343
00:17:38,624 --> 00:17:40,025
Professionals?

344
00:17:41,144 --> 00:17:42,905
Like that woman, Huiling?

345
00:17:45,465 --> 00:17:47,025
How professional?

346
00:17:47,745 --> 00:17:48,544
She's made arrests?

347
00:17:48,544 --> 00:17:49,745
I can't say more.

348
00:17:49,864 --> 00:17:50,745
Strictly speaking,

349
00:17:50,985 --> 00:17:53,905
just standing here drinking with you
is already breaking protocol.

350
00:17:57,745 --> 00:17:59,985
So you're planning
to audit the promoters?

351
00:18:01,945 --> 00:18:05,025
Your department might be
the point of vulnerability.

352
00:18:05,745 --> 00:18:07,905
We stand upright.

353
00:18:07,905 --> 00:18:08,745
Audit away.

354
00:18:10,745 --> 00:18:11,976
Should we change the subject?

355
00:18:13,304 --> 00:18:14,425
One last question.

356
00:18:15,544 --> 00:18:17,025
How far do you intend to go?

357
00:18:20,185 --> 00:18:21,265
Can't even tell me that?

358
00:18:21,265 --> 00:18:22,705
It's not that.

359
00:18:23,344 --> 00:18:24,784
I don't really know.

360
00:18:25,745 --> 00:18:27,544
Internal audits are dynamic.

361
00:18:28,025 --> 00:18:28,824
How we audit,

362
00:18:29,745 --> 00:18:30,824
how it progresses,

363
00:18:31,705 --> 00:18:32,784
and how far we go

364
00:18:33,304 --> 00:18:36,265
entirely depend
on how certain people cooperate.

365
00:19:01,465 --> 00:19:02,384
Ms. Qiao, you're back.

366
00:19:03,344 --> 00:19:03,985
Give it to me.

367
00:19:04,465 --> 00:19:05,304
No, it's fine.

368
00:19:05,304 --> 00:19:06,025
Hand it over.

369
00:19:06,025 --> 00:19:06,705
It's quite heavy.

370
00:19:06,705 --> 00:19:07,144
It's okay.

371
00:19:08,265 --> 00:19:08,905
Easy.

372
00:19:13,665 --> 00:19:14,745
You piled them up for me?

373
00:19:16,064 --> 00:19:16,945
It'd be a hassle

374
00:19:16,945 --> 00:19:18,104
if someone took them.

375
00:19:20,425 --> 00:19:21,465
Thank you.

376
00:19:22,304 --> 00:19:23,665
I'll leave it here then.

377
00:19:24,104 --> 00:19:24,705
Thanks.

378
00:19:24,905 --> 00:19:25,384
No problem.

379
00:19:26,584 --> 00:19:27,144
Thanks.

380
00:20:05,512 --> 00:20:08,968
(RCS project)

381
00:20:45,544 --> 00:20:46,544
Ms. Chen, your package.

382
00:20:46,544 --> 00:20:48,265
Thanks, Fan.

383
00:21:12,064 --> 00:21:15,185
I understand cutting travel
to save costs and boost efficiency.

384
00:21:15,185 --> 00:21:17,064
But the way this is presented is wrong.

385
00:21:17,425 --> 00:21:21,745
It's like the partners are treated
differently from regular employees.

386
00:21:21,745 --> 00:21:22,505
Yeah.

387
00:21:23,025 --> 00:21:25,104
Travel expenses
could be individually budgeted.

388
00:21:25,745 --> 00:21:27,945
I should be free
to choose a three-star hotel

389
00:21:27,945 --> 00:21:29,905
or a five-star one.

390
00:21:29,905 --> 00:21:31,225
It's my own expenses.

391
00:21:32,104 --> 00:21:33,945
Anyway, that's what I'll say later.

392
00:21:34,985 --> 00:21:35,584
And you?

393
00:21:35,905 --> 00:21:36,745
Your opinion?

394
00:21:37,185 --> 00:21:37,945
So boring.

395
00:21:39,824 --> 00:21:40,505
What did you say?

396
00:21:45,505 --> 00:21:46,304
What did you say?

397
00:21:51,425 --> 00:21:52,064
Dongming.

398
00:21:52,624 --> 00:21:53,864
I need to tell you something.

399
00:21:54,304 --> 00:21:55,425
Brace yourself.

400
00:21:58,665 --> 00:21:59,584
You want to tell me

401
00:22:00,185 --> 00:22:01,705
that you don't love your wife,

402
00:22:01,705 --> 00:22:02,665
but me, huh?

403
00:22:03,544 --> 00:22:04,344
I have cancer.

404
00:22:07,144 --> 00:22:07,905
Get out of here.

405
00:22:08,584 --> 00:22:09,544
You have cancer?

406
00:22:09,544 --> 00:22:10,665
Are you kidding me?

407
00:22:11,985 --> 00:22:13,784
You run those half and full marathons.

408
00:22:13,784 --> 00:22:14,465
You have cancer?

409
00:22:14,665 --> 00:22:16,505
I'd believe you
if you said your legs hurt.

410
00:22:16,505 --> 00:22:18,144
I didn't believe it at first either.

411
00:22:18,584 --> 00:22:20,544
But I had to believe it
after seeing the report.

412
00:22:23,025 --> 00:22:25,104
There's a tumor on my bladder.

413
00:22:25,905 --> 00:22:26,665
Pretty big.

414
00:22:27,824 --> 00:22:30,384
I thought that if I got cancer,

415
00:22:30,544 --> 00:22:31,544
it would be liver cancer.

416
00:22:32,064 --> 00:22:33,256
From exhaustion and drinking.

417
00:22:34,025 --> 00:22:34,784
I never expected

418
00:22:36,784 --> 00:22:38,344
to get bladder cancer.

419
00:22:42,784 --> 00:22:45,304
Y-You found out in your physical exam?

420
00:22:46,425 --> 00:22:47,945
T-Those aren't always accurate.

421
00:22:47,945 --> 00:22:48,824
Follow up on it.

422
00:22:48,824 --> 00:22:49,584
I did.

423
00:22:49,945 --> 00:22:50,945
I saw a specialist.

424
00:22:51,705 --> 00:22:53,104
The report came out this morning.

425
00:22:53,985 --> 00:22:56,425
The doctor advised me to have surgery
as soon as possible.

426
00:22:58,705 --> 00:23:00,304
T-Then take leave now.

427
00:23:00,304 --> 00:23:01,384
No, I can't.

428
00:23:01,505 --> 00:23:03,225
I've almost closed the deal with Dongyu.

429
00:23:03,225 --> 00:23:05,104
Taking leave now
would ruin all my progress.

430
00:23:06,745 --> 00:23:07,705
I can't take leave.

431
00:23:08,864 --> 00:23:11,665
Dongming, you're the only one I trust.

432
00:23:12,265 --> 00:23:13,624
Keep this secret for me.

433
00:23:14,864 --> 00:23:15,505
Let's go.

434
00:23:21,624 --> 00:23:22,465
In my opinion,

435
00:23:23,945 --> 00:23:25,144
big companies

436
00:23:26,425 --> 00:23:27,265
are working

437
00:23:28,544 --> 00:23:31,544
tirelessly on EHS and ESG.

438
00:23:32,705 --> 00:23:32,985
Yes.

439
00:23:33,225 --> 00:23:35,344
They're driven
by a sense of responsibility.

440
00:23:36,505 --> 00:23:37,185
But frankly,

441
00:23:37,905 --> 00:23:41,544
aren't they also building a moat
to outpace competitors?

442
00:23:43,225 --> 00:23:44,824
So what should Ruijin do now?

443
00:23:47,265 --> 00:23:51,025
We must keep a close eye
on these companies.

444
00:23:51,705 --> 00:23:54,784
We need to constantly push their limits.

445
00:23:55,624 --> 00:23:56,824
We must make them realize

446
00:23:57,104 --> 00:24:00,745
that we are their most reliable
and trusted support.

447
00:24:01,225 --> 00:24:05,304
Only Ruijin can help them build

448
00:24:06,144 --> 00:24:08,505
an unbreakable moat.

449
00:24:11,425 --> 00:24:11,905
Xiao Yang.

450
00:24:12,265 --> 00:24:12,824
Xiao Yang.

451
00:24:15,344 --> 00:24:16,025
What's wrong?

452
00:24:16,025 --> 00:24:17,025
What's going on here?

453
00:24:17,425 --> 00:24:18,505
What happened?

454
00:24:18,985 --> 00:24:20,025
Too much pressure.

455
00:24:20,025 --> 00:24:20,824
That must be it.

456
00:24:21,384 --> 00:24:22,344
He's doing well lately.

457
00:24:26,505 --> 00:24:27,745
- Get up.
- Get up.

458
00:24:34,784 --> 00:24:35,304
Mr. Li.

459
00:24:36,425 --> 00:24:37,025
You're back.

460
00:24:37,864 --> 00:24:39,144
We had the debrief last night.

461
00:24:39,144 --> 00:24:40,144
I rushed back today

462
00:24:40,505 --> 00:24:41,505
to report to you.

463
00:24:43,265 --> 00:24:43,824
Come in.

464
00:24:52,344 --> 00:24:53,584
How did it go?

465
00:25:10,665 --> 00:25:11,784
I missed you every day

466
00:25:13,344 --> 00:25:14,384
during my trip.

467
00:25:23,864 --> 00:25:24,985
I was wrong.

468
00:25:31,985 --> 00:25:32,905
Be more specific.

469
00:25:35,945 --> 00:25:37,344
I shouldn't have

470
00:25:37,344 --> 00:25:38,225
acted on my own.

471
00:25:40,185 --> 00:25:41,185
I understand now.

472
00:25:43,505 --> 00:25:47,344
I promise I won't make the same mistake.

473
00:25:50,185 --> 00:25:51,265
I'll listen to you.

474
00:25:55,985 --> 00:25:56,824
You will?

475
00:26:00,104 --> 00:26:00,705
Let go.

476
00:26:26,945 --> 00:26:27,624
I'll go first.

477
00:26:27,624 --> 00:26:28,265
Wait.

478
00:26:34,304 --> 00:26:35,304
Remember your promise.

479
00:26:38,985 --> 00:26:39,544
Absolutely.

480
00:27:04,624 --> 00:27:05,745
You're back from Hubei?

481
00:27:06,344 --> 00:27:06,745
Yeah.

482
00:27:08,745 --> 00:27:10,745
You look great.

483
00:27:12,705 --> 00:27:13,185
Really?

484
00:27:13,624 --> 00:27:14,104
Yeah.

485
00:27:55,624 --> 00:27:59,425
(Like a cat chased by its owner,
desperately fleeing,)

486
00:28:00,745 --> 00:28:03,824
(yet secretly yearning to be caught,)

487
00:28:04,864 --> 00:28:05,864
(I have to say,)

488
00:28:07,104 --> 00:28:08,985
(I think I'm starting
to like this feeling.)

489
00:28:08,985 --> 00:28:10,225
(Like)

490
00:28:10,225 --> 00:28:14,304
(I wonder if you feel the same way.)

491
00:28:16,144 --> 00:28:17,544
I saw Qiao Hailun earlier.

492
00:28:17,824 --> 00:28:18,705
Qiao Hailun?

493
00:28:18,905 --> 00:28:20,104
The one under Mr. Li.

494
00:28:20,425 --> 00:28:20,985
Yeah.

495
00:28:21,265 --> 00:28:22,985
Wasn't she exiled?

496
00:28:23,384 --> 00:28:24,465
She's back so soon?

497
00:28:25,304 --> 00:28:27,064
She has her ways.

498
00:28:27,705 --> 00:28:29,185
Flirting and acting cute.

499
00:28:29,544 --> 00:28:31,185
Men eat that up.

500
00:28:33,064 --> 00:28:34,465
Want to learn it too?

501
00:28:35,225 --> 00:28:37,265
That's disgusting. I'd never do that.

502
00:28:52,505 --> 00:28:53,544
It's my song.

503
00:28:53,824 --> 00:28:54,425
Hurry up.

504
00:28:54,425 --> 00:28:54,864
Drink up.

505
00:28:57,719 --> 00:29:00,033
♪The story isn't over yet♪

506
00:29:00,864 --> 00:29:03,505
Look, Mr. Dong.

507
00:29:03,945 --> 00:29:06,584
Mr. Jin used to be
such a straight-laced guy.

508
00:29:06,584 --> 00:29:08,824
Look at him now,
all hugs with Liang Danning.

509
00:29:08,824 --> 00:29:11,425
Sometimes I really wish
I were a woman too.

510
00:29:13,745 --> 00:29:15,784
Well, you can wait for reincarnation.

511
00:29:16,185 --> 00:29:17,864
Mr. Dong, you can still joke around?

512
00:29:18,465 --> 00:29:19,905
I'm so worried.

513
00:29:20,304 --> 00:29:22,408
What if she actually becomes Mrs. Shen?

514
00:29:22,408 --> 00:29:23,225
Stop chit-chatting.

515
00:29:23,225 --> 00:29:24,104
Let's drink.

516
00:29:24,104 --> 00:29:24,745
Yeah.

517
00:29:24,745 --> 00:29:25,425
Come on.

518
00:29:25,425 --> 00:29:25,864
Cheers.

519
00:29:26,945 --> 00:29:27,425
- Come on.
- Cheers.

520
00:29:35,265 --> 00:29:35,665
Mr. Shen.

521
00:29:36,552 --> 00:29:37,576
I came to pick up Liang.

522
00:29:38,985 --> 00:29:39,985
At 318, over here.

523
00:29:42,824 --> 00:29:43,864
Tang Lide got taken down.

524
00:29:44,465 --> 00:29:45,344
I thought it was you.

525
00:29:46,665 --> 00:29:47,304
No.

526
00:29:48,344 --> 00:29:51,104
Barry caught him faking sales numbers.

527
00:29:52,225 --> 00:29:53,465
It can't be a coincidence.

528
00:29:54,864 --> 00:29:56,384
If no one brought it up,

529
00:29:56,705 --> 00:29:57,784
how would Barry know?

530
00:29:58,864 --> 00:30:00,505
I'm not really interested.

531
00:30:01,425 --> 00:30:03,465
Tang Lide was utterly useless.

532
00:30:04,824 --> 00:30:06,265
You haven't been here in a while.

533
00:30:06,792 --> 00:30:07,528
I wanted to come

534
00:30:07,528 --> 00:30:09,144
but you might not be happy to see me.

535
00:30:09,784 --> 00:30:10,665
That's quite honest.

536
00:30:12,064 --> 00:30:12,665
Listen.

537
00:30:13,225 --> 00:30:16,025
Are you sure you can't
get back with Shen Xing?

538
00:30:17,584 --> 00:30:18,824
We're just not meant to be.

539
00:30:19,912 --> 00:30:21,256
I can't give her what she wants.

540
00:30:21,665 --> 00:30:22,504
And she doesn't care

541
00:30:23,265 --> 00:30:24,104
about what I want.

542
00:30:25,384 --> 00:30:26,384
But anyway,

543
00:30:27,864 --> 00:30:30,425
Mr. Shen, I truly appreciate you.

544
00:30:30,624 --> 00:30:33,144
I hope you'll continue to support me.

545
00:30:33,784 --> 00:30:34,905
Is that what you think?

546
00:30:36,985 --> 00:30:39,225
Now Tang Lide's been taken out.

547
00:30:40,265 --> 00:30:41,384
Barry supports Zhao Mei.

548
00:30:42,104 --> 00:30:43,864
If you want to climb higher,

549
00:30:44,225 --> 00:30:45,225
you need my backing.

550
00:30:46,225 --> 00:30:48,784
But you refuse to date Shen Xing.

551
00:30:50,185 --> 00:30:52,784
So make another offer.

552
00:30:53,505 --> 00:30:55,144
Give me a reason to help you.

553
00:31:08,344 --> 00:31:09,416
Why did you drink so much?

554
00:31:10,425 --> 00:31:11,624
I was happy today

555
00:31:11,905 --> 00:31:13,185
and got carried away.

556
00:31:13,584 --> 00:31:14,705
What made you so happy?

557
00:31:15,705 --> 00:31:17,425
I closed a deal.

558
00:31:18,144 --> 00:31:19,465
That calls for celebration.

559
00:31:20,665 --> 00:31:23,025
My place or should I take you home?

560
00:31:23,144 --> 00:31:24,505
Let's go...

561
00:31:25,745 --> 00:31:27,225
Have a problem with my place?

562
00:31:27,624 --> 00:31:28,584
You hate to go there.

563
00:31:28,584 --> 00:31:29,864
There's a dog next door.

564
00:31:29,985 --> 00:31:31,144
I'm scared.

565
00:31:33,225 --> 00:31:34,384
- Be careful.
- Hurry.

566
00:31:34,665 --> 00:31:35,985
Let's go.

567
00:31:37,104 --> 00:31:37,945
Slow down.

568
00:31:38,144 --> 00:31:38,985
Let's go.

569
00:32:04,648 --> 00:32:12,076
(Causes of right-sided
abdominal pain in males)

570
00:32:12,076 --> 00:32:19,496
(Appendicitis, Typhlitis...)

571
00:33:07,465 --> 00:33:08,033
Hello.

572
00:33:08,905 --> 00:33:10,304
You stayed out all night?

573
00:33:10,905 --> 00:33:11,425
I came home.

574
00:33:11,905 --> 00:33:12,745
After two.

575
00:33:13,624 --> 00:33:15,624
I have a training session
with Connie this morning.

576
00:33:16,064 --> 00:33:17,104
So I got up early.

577
00:33:19,064 --> 00:33:19,624
That's that.

578
00:33:21,465 --> 00:33:23,025
That's way too early.

579
00:33:32,864 --> 00:33:33,624
Let's continue.

580
00:33:36,265 --> 00:33:37,344
You're absolutely right.

581
00:33:37,945 --> 00:33:40,985
This management training
we're doing now is absurd.

582
00:33:41,505 --> 00:33:42,745
In this world,

583
00:33:42,985 --> 00:33:44,265
some people are sick,

584
00:33:44,745 --> 00:33:45,905
some are starving,

585
00:33:46,425 --> 00:33:48,225
yet here we are discussing management.

586
00:33:49,185 --> 00:33:53,185
The truth is,
hardly anyone manages themselves well.

587
00:33:53,985 --> 00:33:54,784
For example,

588
00:33:56,465 --> 00:33:59,624
I've warned myself countless times
to be patient with my child.

589
00:33:59,824 --> 00:34:02,025
But every time I get home,

590
00:34:02,025 --> 00:34:03,624
I see my kid covered in mud.

591
00:34:04,144 --> 00:34:05,465
The kindergarten teacher calls me

592
00:34:05,465 --> 00:34:08,264
to meet her the next morning.

593
00:34:08,664 --> 00:34:10,704
But I happen to have a meeting then.

594
00:34:10,704 --> 00:34:12,425
Of course I lose my temper.

595
00:34:13,425 --> 00:34:14,264
You really need to

596
00:34:14,264 --> 00:34:15,505
see through things.

597
00:34:16,425 --> 00:34:19,305
That distinction between work and life
doesn't exist.

598
00:34:20,144 --> 00:34:22,064
If you want to go further,

599
00:34:22,584 --> 00:34:24,425
learn to be yourself.

600
00:34:25,104 --> 00:34:26,345
You can't fake it forever.

601
00:34:26,785 --> 00:34:29,144
(Yeah, how long can I keep this up?)

602
00:34:30,064 --> 00:34:33,505
(The real question is,
what's the point of faking it?)

603
00:34:34,184 --> 00:34:35,224
Give me the address.

604
00:34:36,224 --> 00:34:37,224
I can get there.

605
00:34:37,865 --> 00:34:39,345
Yeah, okay.

606
00:34:40,425 --> 00:34:41,064
See you tonight.

607
00:34:43,465 --> 00:34:45,985
You're really going to
meet those small distributors?

608
00:34:46,144 --> 00:34:47,664
They're very folk.

609
00:34:47,905 --> 00:34:48,985
Is that a problem?

610
00:34:50,144 --> 00:34:51,825
Someone might be unhappy.

611
00:34:52,305 --> 00:34:53,345
You mean Shen Mo?

612
00:34:56,624 --> 00:34:57,465
You know what?

613
00:34:58,305 --> 00:35:00,425
All these years in China,

614
00:35:01,385 --> 00:35:05,224
I've never reached out
to those small distributors.

615
00:35:06,345 --> 00:35:08,825
Because I've been waiting
for the right moment.

616
00:35:12,425 --> 00:35:14,064
The moment to break the monopoly.

617
00:35:14,744 --> 00:35:18,056
You know, those small traditional
off-trade outlets

618
00:35:18,056 --> 00:35:20,544
contribute a huge chunk
of our annual revenue.

619
00:35:20,825 --> 00:35:21,928
But here's the thing.

620
00:35:21,928 --> 00:35:23,945
We don't have a direct connection
with them.

621
00:35:24,985 --> 00:35:28,025
The information is strictly controlled
by those large wholesalers,

622
00:35:28,104 --> 00:35:28,985
like Shen Mo.

623
00:35:29,384 --> 00:35:31,985
And then there are those seller folks
of the commercial department

624
00:35:31,985 --> 00:35:33,025
like Xu Yuntian.

625
00:35:34,264 --> 00:35:36,184
I'm the Managing Director of GST,

626
00:35:36,744 --> 00:35:39,264
but the information I get
from those guys is pretty filtered.

627
00:35:40,392 --> 00:35:42,408
They basically make their own rules
of the market

628
00:35:42,408 --> 00:35:43,912
and I'm left completely in the dark.

629
00:35:44,544 --> 00:35:47,104
They tell me what price
I should sell Gennadiy 25 for.

630
00:35:48,224 --> 00:35:49,385
And what choice do I have?

631
00:35:50,664 --> 00:35:52,825
You think I'm the boss of GST China?

632
00:35:53,624 --> 00:35:56,264
They're the ones calling the shots.

633
00:35:56,744 --> 00:36:00,144
It does sound quite displeasing.

634
00:36:00,704 --> 00:36:01,905
That's an understatement.

635
00:36:03,544 --> 00:36:05,624
Breaking a monopoly takes time.

636
00:36:07,425 --> 00:36:09,064
My old boss once told me,

637
00:36:10,264 --> 00:36:13,345
"All collapses start from within."

638
00:36:14,184 --> 00:36:16,144
China has a similar saying,

639
00:36:16,264 --> 00:36:17,345
"A long dike collapses"

640
00:36:17,865 --> 00:36:18,985
"from an ant hole."

641
00:36:21,785 --> 00:36:24,704
I need to find that "ant hole."

642
00:36:26,425 --> 00:36:27,144
Dong Yue.

643
00:36:29,184 --> 00:36:30,704
He's been visiting you frequently.

644
00:36:30,825 --> 00:36:33,184
I bet he's clashing with Shen Mo.

645
00:36:34,104 --> 00:36:34,664
Of course,

646
00:36:35,465 --> 00:36:37,584
where there's profit, there's conflict.

647
00:36:38,184 --> 00:36:40,664
So you ask if Shen Mo will be upset?

648
00:36:41,064 --> 00:36:43,505
What's bound to happen will happen.

649
00:36:45,425 --> 00:36:47,064
But compared to Zhao Mei,

650
00:36:47,744 --> 00:36:49,345
I do prefer Dong Yue a bit more.

651
00:36:49,505 --> 00:36:50,104
Why?

652
00:36:52,144 --> 00:36:54,184
We're heading to a KTV later.

653
00:36:54,544 --> 00:36:55,064
I know.

654
00:36:55,264 --> 00:36:56,264
I'll make arrangements.

655
00:36:57,664 --> 00:37:01,144
On second thought, you shouldn't come.

656
00:37:01,825 --> 00:37:02,632
It's inconvenient.

657
00:37:04,264 --> 00:37:07,425
That's why I prefer Dong Yue.

658
00:37:18,985 --> 00:37:20,264
This is Mr. Zhuang Zhiqiang.

659
00:37:20,425 --> 00:37:22,064
He came all the way from another city.

660
00:37:22,905 --> 00:37:23,785
Nice to meet you.

661
00:37:23,785 --> 00:37:25,144
I've heard so much about you.

662
00:37:25,664 --> 00:37:27,505
Thank you for managing our business.

663
00:37:27,704 --> 00:37:28,465
I'm flattered.

664
00:37:28,664 --> 00:37:30,465
Your products are exceptional.

665
00:37:31,104 --> 00:37:32,224
Here, let me toast to you.

666
00:37:32,224 --> 00:37:32,624
Come on.

667
00:37:32,624 --> 00:37:33,785
I'm counting on your support.

668
00:37:34,425 --> 00:37:34,945
Mr. Dong.

669
